      title_content: 'How to stay active while studying at home',
      body_content:
        '<div class="entry-inner">\n<p><strong>From reading to meditating; painting to baking, there are so many ways to keep busy while we&rsquo;re all spending more time at home &ndash;&nbsp;but perhaps the most important is some form of daily exercise.</strong></p>\n<h2>Why is it important to stay active when studying from home?</h2>\n<iframe class="giphy-embed" src="https://giphy.com/embed/ida2Uus6lvTmU" width="480" height="270" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<p>Even if you don&rsquo;t do much exercise normally, keeping active has lots of other benefits &ndash; especially when you&rsquo;re studying from home. Light, regular exercise can:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>improve your concentration</li>\n<li>help you be more productive</li>\n<li>give you a boost of happy endorphins</li>\n<li>make sure you get a proper night&rsquo;s sleep</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There&rsquo;s no need to do a full-on bootcamp workout every day, but we&rsquo;ve put together a few ideas to help you make movement part of your daily routine. This is the perfect time to try new activities &ndash; and who knows, you might find your new favourite hobby!</p>\n<p>From barely any effort to a more strenuous workout, here are six ways to stay active while studying at home:</p>\n<h2>Stand up more</h2>\n<iframe class="giphy-embed" src="https://giphy.com/embed/3oz8xysJuWtO9UgUlG" width="480" height="240" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<p>Probably the easiest and most accessible way to stay active is simply to get up and walk around a bit! At least once an hour is recommended, but do it as often as you like &ndash; just set a timer to remind you. You should feel refreshed, energised, and ready to focus on your work again.</p>\n<p>Try a reminder-setting app such as Randomly RemindMe, StandUp &ndash; the Work Breaker Timer or Move &ndash; Daily Activity to Stay Healthy.</p>\n<p>There are lots of other ways to increase your activity little-and-often &ndash; so little that you&rsquo;ll hardly even notice it. If you&rsquo;re on the phone, have a wander as you talk &ndash; and I&rsquo;m pretty sure walking to the kitchen to grab a snack counts, too!</p>\n<h2>Interactive gym classes</h2>\n<div class="tenor-gif-embed" style="width: 100%; position: relative;" data-postid="16759838" data-share-method="host" data-width="100%" data-aspect-ratio="0.9899598393574296" data-processed="true">\n<div style="padding-top: 101.01419878296147%;"><iframe style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;" src="https://tenor.com/embed/16759838?canonicalurl=https://blog.intostudy.com/living-abroad/lifestyle/how-to-stay-active-while-studying-at-home/" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n<p>Since the schools have closed, children around the UK are now being taught lessons at home &ndash; including gym and PE. To the delight of parents across the country, popular fitness coach Joe Wicks has been streaming interactive gym sessions at 9am every weekday via his <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAxW1XT0iEJo0TYlRfn6rYQ">YouTube channel</a>.</p>\n<p>Joe&rsquo;s sessions might have started out as an activity for children, but with millions of viewers tuning in every day, they&rsquo;re proving to be a hit with people of all ages! The exercises are designed to require very little space and no equipment &ndash; so they&rsquo;re perfect for keeping active at home.</p>\n<h2>The 7-minute workout</h2>\n<iframe class="giphy-embed" src="https://giphy.com/embed/2A5A9uJBzgyty" width="480" height="209" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<p>Working towards a deadline, but still want to make time to exercise? If you want to get as much activity in as little time as possible, the 7-minute workout is a great option. Based on a sequence of&nbsp;12 simple exercises, it focuses on high-intensity interval training &ndash; and the sequence can be altered to work different muscle groups.</p>\n<div class="mailmunch-forms-in-post-middle" style="display: none !important;">&nbsp;</div>\n<p>If you fancy trying it yourself, there are plenty of guided 7-minute workouts to follow on YouTube &ndash; or you could download the <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.popularapp.sevenmins&amp;hl=en_GB">Google app</a> to your phone.</p>\n<h2>YouTube yoga sessions</h2>\n<div class="tenor-gif-embed" style="width: 100%; position: relative;" data-postid="13026289" data-share-method="host" data-width="100%" data-aspect-ratio="1.7785714285714287" data-processed="true">\n<div style="padding-top: 56.22489959839358%;"><iframe style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;" src="https://tenor.com/embed/13026289?canonicalurl=https://blog.intostudy.com/living-abroad/lifestyle/how-to-stay-active-while-studying-at-home/" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n<p>As well as being a great way to exercise, yoga is widely believed to make you happier, improve your focus and relax your mind &ndash; all of which are more important than ever when studying at home.</p>\n<p>Thankfully, whether you&rsquo;re a yoga fanatic or a complete beginner, there are so many resources available online. Try <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/yogawithadriene/videos">Yoga With Adriene</a> &ndash; a hugely popular YouTube series with more than six million subscribers, and accessible routines for all abilities.</p>\n<h2>Fitness gaming fun</h2>\n<iframe class="giphy-embed" src="https://giphy.com/embed/ZwrSh17PHByrjsLvmd" width="480" height="198" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<p>If you&rsquo;re lucky enough to own a gaming console, there are countless interactive fitness games available &ndash; you might even have some already! Whether you prefer Kinect Sports Rivals for the Xbox One, Ring Fit Adventure for the Nintendo Switch or BOXVR for the Playstation 4, you&rsquo;re sure to find a fitness game to suit you and your console.</p>\n<h2>Get your clean on</h2>\n<iframe class="giphy-embed" src="https://giphy.com/embed/RNDdIRbOM7hKH9ezKz" width="480" height="204" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<p>A tidy space equals a tidy mind, so why not get productive while you move and give your room a spring clean? It might not sound like much, but cleaning increases your heart rate and burns calories &ndash; and with a sparkling space in which to work, your studying will improve too!</p>\n<p>Vigorous housework for 30 minutes (that&rsquo;s if you really work up a sweat!) has the same effect as a brisk walk for the same length of time, but you&rsquo;ll have finished the washing up at the end of it. A win-win situation, if you ask us!</p>\n</div>',
